# Windows Server 2019 VM Creation
1. Install the required ISOs to local machine, in this case ISOs needed: Windows Server 2019 and virti0-win (for functionality)
  - Got Windows Server ISO from https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/evalcenter/download-windows-server-2019
  - Got virtio-win from https://fedorapeople.org/groups/virt/virtio-win/direct-downloads/archive-virtio/virtio-win-0.1.285-1/virtio-win.iso 
2. Create the VM
  - selected the desired node for installation (devops-nitrogen)
  - Right click the chosen node and select create VM or go to top right and select create VM button
  - Proceed through the installation options:
    * General Tab
      - Select node (devops-nitrogen)
      - Select VM ID (1046)
      - Select Name for VM (MercerWin2019)
      - Select resource pool (Interns)
      - Click next
    * OS Tab
      - Select local storage
      - Select ISO (SERVER_EVAL_x64FRE_en-us.iso)
      - Select type as Microsoft Windows
      - Select version 10/2016/2019
      - Check the box for Add additional drive for VirtIO drivers
      - Choose local storage
      - Select virtio-win-0.1.285.iso
      - Click next
    * System Tab
      - Leave all default
      - Click next    
    * Disks Tab
      - Confirmed correct bus storage
      - Choose storage local
      - Choose desired amount of storage (60gb)
      - Click next
    * CPU Tab
      - Chose 1 socket
      - 4 cores
      - type x86-64-v2-AES
      - Click next
    * Memory Tab
      - Choose desired RAM (8192)
      - Click next
    * Network Tab
      - Changed bridge to vmbr0
      - Click next
    * Confirm Tab
      - Confirm settings and hit finish
3. Windows Installation
  - Proceed through the installtion wizard
  - When prompted to choose where to install windows went to vioscsi > 2k19 > amd64
* Virti0 setup
  - Open file explorer
  - Go to this pc > virtio-win drive > open drive and select virtio-win-gt-x64
  - Go through the wizard and always select vioscsi when possible
4. Complete

